records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jean M Ericksen in court with attorney Sarah A Ponath.  Brian J. Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads guilty to count # 1.  Court finds the defendant guilty of count #1.  Count #2 is dismissed and read in.  State gives recommendations.  Attorney Ponath makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.
The Court Orders the Following: Count #1
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
100 Days Huber with STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.  (Credit - 0 days).  Concurrent to 15CM1906
Term of Probation: 1 Year
Conditions of Probation:
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of illegal controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
Inform agent of all prescriptions;
Inform treatment providers of probation and charges
Maintain/Obtain employment;
To avoid any person or place associated with the sale, distrubution, or use of illegal controlled substances. 
Condition Time: 15 days STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion
COSTS:  $243.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
